category.name: movements/politics
description:
Swedizen - a Non-state Voluntary Initiative - is a group for anyone interested in creating future stateless cryptonations and open governance. This specific group is based in Stockholm, Sweden, and will try to establish a local "Bitnation compatible" group of people to begin with.


"In the multi-local society, communities and places are junctions of a network, points of connection among short networks, which generate and regenerate the local social and production fabric and long networks, which connect that place and that community with the rest of the world (De Rita, Bonomi, 1998)."

WHAT IT IS:

- Pseudo-anonymous or actual identification of a person, and proof-of-existence.

- Encrypted, trust-based.

- Using GnuPG, NFC and QR technologies.

- Possibility to restore lost password through trusted parties.


WHAT IT'S NOT:

- It is not Government issued or considered a valid form of ID in any state.

- Not a payment system

- Not a cryptocurrency  (and does not need one)

- Not anything money-ish
name: Swedizen Non-state Voluntary Initiative and Cryptonation

description:
Anyone who wants to learn more about Effective Altruism, get to know other people who are passionate about having a positive impact in the world and wants to have deep intriguing discussions should definitely join us! Effective Altruism is a philosophy and social movement which is all about answering one simple question: How can we use our resources to help others as much as possible? Rather than just doing what feels right, we use evidence and careful analysis to find the very best causes to work on. This can apply to everything from where to donate your charity money to future career choice. For more information, please check out the following websites:


https://www.effectivealtruism.org/
http://effektivaltruism.org/
https://80000hours.org/

description:
Det här är en grupp för alla som är intresserade av filosofin, praktiken eller ekonomin och vetenskapen bakom individuell frihet och ett fritt samhälle.


Här tar vi upp roliga engagemang och tilställningar för de som gillar frihet: öl- och disussionskvällar, debatter, aktivism och fester, eller något annat som någon tycker skulle vara intressant att göra.


Om du är intresserad av libertarianism, anarkokapitalism, agorism, minarkism, utträde ur staten, frihetliga lösningar på komplexa samhällsproblem och gillar att träffa andra som delar den politiska inställningar är det här en perfekt grupp för dig.

description:
Meetup med alle interesserede i åben offentlig data. Koderne, de offentligt ansatte, designerne, akademikerne, entreprenørerne. Kun ved at forbinde og udforske mulighederne sammen bliver det muligt at tilgængeliggøre mere data og skabe eksempler, der vil få andre statslige organisationer til at indse potentialet i åben offentlig data.

Meet-up with all those interested in open government data. The coders, the civil servants, the designers, the academics, the entrepreneurs. Only by connecting and exploring steps together will it be possible to both get more data available, as well as build the examples that will make other government organisations see the potential of open government data.

category.name: movements/politics
description:
Vi vil gerne invitere alle mennesker som ønsker at forandre og påvirke måden vi arbejder på i virksomhederne. De der synes arbejde er noget man gør, og ikke et sted man tager hen. Hvis du har det sådan vil du synes det er interessant at deltage i vores arrangementer og bidrage til diskussionerne vi har på vores meetups.

Hvis du er typen som konstant forsøger at påvirke kulturen i din virksomhed fra de faste planlagte rammer til en mere eksperimenterende samarbejdsform, fra at være kontrolleret mod at være mere autonom – så er #ResponsiveOrg et forum for dig.

Vi vil gerne bringe innovative forandrings-søgende mennesker sammen til #responsivecoffee og andre #responsiveorg arrangementer. Vi håber at du vil dele erfaringer og få ny viden du kan tage med hjem til din virksomhed, og at du får indsigt i hvilke metoder, betingelser og kommunikationsplatforme der kan anvendes for at opnå en Responsive Organisation. Og vi vil gerne dele praktiske erfaringer med at implementere disse.

Kundernes behov og vaner ændrer sig hurtigt, og det kan være enormt svært at følge med som virksomhed, og skabe den forandring og udvikling i virksomheden der er nødvendig for at følge kundernes tempo. The Responsive Organisation meetup er en samling af mennesker som deler og drøfter hvordan de hver især sætter retning og nye standarder for hvordan virksomheder lærer af og tilpasser sig de forandringer der sker i verden. - se ResponsiveOrg præsentation

Vi synes det skal diskuteres face-to-face hvordan vi håndterer det i København – Danmark. Du kan læse mere om Responsive Organisation initiativet her http://www.theresponsiveorg.com/

Vi glæder os til at se dig til vores arrangementer.
name: #ResponsiveOrg Copenhagen

category.name: movements/politics
description:
Swedizen - a Non-state Voluntary Initiative - is a group for anyone interested in creating future stateless cryptonations and open governance. This specific group is based in Stockholm, Sweden, and will try to establish a local "Bitnation compatible" group of people to begin with.


"In the multi-local society, communities and places are junctions of a network, points of connection among short networks, which generate and regenerate the local social and production fabric and long networks, which connect that place and that community with the rest of the world (De Rita, Bonomi, 1998)."

WHAT IT IS:

- Pseudo-anonymous or actual identification of a person, and proof-of-existence.

- Encrypted, trust-based.

- Using GnuPG, NFC and QR technologies.

- Possibility to restore lost password through trusted parties.


WHAT IT'S NOT:

- It is not Government issued or considered a valid form of ID in any state.

- Not a payment system

- Not a cryptocurrency  (and does not need one)

- Not anything money-ish
name: Swedizen Non-state Voluntary Initiative and Cryptonation

description:
Anyone who wants to learn more about Effective Altruism, get to know other people who are passionate about having a positive impact in the world and wants to have deep intriguing discussions should definitely join us! Effective Altruism is a philosophy and social movement which is all about answering one simple question: How can we use our resources to help others as much as possible? Rather than just doing what feels right, we use evidence and careful analysis to find the very best causes to work on. This can apply to everything from where to donate your charity money to future career choice. For more information, please check out the following websites:


https://www.effectivealtruism.org/
http://effektivaltruism.org/

category.name: movements/politics
description:
Swedizen - a Non-state Voluntary Initiative - is a group for anyone interested in creating future stateless cryptonations and open governance. This specific group is based in Stockholm, Sweden, and will try to establish a local "Bitnation compatible" group of people to begin with.


"In the multi-local society, communities and places are junctions of a network, points of connection among short networks, which generate and regenerate the local social and production fabric and long networks, which connect that place and that community with the rest of the world (De Rita, Bonomi, 1998)."

WHAT IT IS:

- Pseudo-anonymous or actual identification of a person, and proof-of-existence.

- Encrypted, trust-based.

- Using GnuPG, NFC and QR technologies.

- Possibility to restore lost password through trusted parties.


WHAT IT'S NOT:

- It is not Government issued or considered a valid form of ID in any state.

- Not a payment system

- Not a cryptocurrency  (and does not need one)

- Not anything money-ish
name: Swedizen Non-state Voluntary Initiative and Cryptonation

description:
Anyone who wants to learn more about Effective Altruism, get to know other people who are passionate about having a positive impact in the world and wants to have deep intriguing discussions should definitely join us! Effective Altruism is a philosophy and social movement which is all about answering one simple question: How can we use our resources to help others as much as possible? Rather than just doing what feels right, we use evidence and careful analysis to find the very best causes to work on. This can apply to everything from where to donate your charity money to future career choice. For more information, please check out the following websites:


https://www.effectivealtruism.org/
http://effektivaltruism.org/
https://80000hours.org/

description:
Meetup med alle interesserede i åben offentlig data. Koderne, de offentligt ansatte, designerne, akademikerne, entreprenørerne. Kun ved at forbinde og udforske mulighederne sammen bliver det muligt at tilgængeliggøre mere data og skabe eksempler, der vil få andre statslige organisationer til at indse potentialet i åben offentlig data.

Meet-up with all those interested in open government data. The coders, the civil servants, the designers, the academics, the entrepreneurs. Only by connecting and exploring steps together will it be possible to both get more data available, as well as build the examples that will make other government organisations see the potential of open government data.

Data Drinks: Where (free) beer is transmogrified into free data!

When you Tweet about CPH Data Drinks please use the tag #cphdd

category.name: movements/politics
description:
Vi vil gerne invitere alle mennesker som ønsker at forandre og påvirke måden vi arbejder på i virksomhederne. De der synes arbejde er noget man gør, og ikke et sted man tager hen. Hvis du har det sådan vil du synes det er interessant at deltage i vores arrangementer og bidrage til diskussionerne vi har på vores meetups.

Hvis du er typen som konstant forsøger at påvirke kulturen i din virksomhed fra de faste planlagte rammer til en mere eksperimenterende samarbejdsform, fra at være kontrolleret mod at være mere autonom – så er #ResponsiveOrg et forum for dig.

Vi vil gerne bringe innovative forandrings-søgende mennesker sammen til #responsivecoffee og andre #responsiveorg arrangementer. Vi håber at du vil dele erfaringer og få ny viden du kan tage med hjem til din virksomhed, og at du får indsigt i hvilke metoder, betingelser og kommunikationsplatforme der kan anvendes for at opnå en Responsive Organisation. Og vi vil gerne dele praktiske erfaringer med at implementere disse.

Kundernes behov og vaner ændrer sig hurtigt, og det kan være enormt svært at følge med som virksomhed, og skabe den forandring og udvikling i virksomheden der er nødvendig for at følge kundernes tempo. The Responsive Organisation meetup er en samling af mennesker som deler og drøfter hvordan de hver især sætter retning og nye standarder for hvordan virksomheder lærer af og tilpasser sig de forandringer der sker i verden. - se ResponsiveOrg præsentation

Vi synes det skal diskuteres face-to-face hvordan vi håndterer det i København – Danmark. Du kan læse mere om Responsive Organisation initiativet her http://www.theresponsiveorg.com/

Vi glæder os til at se dig til vores arrangementer.
name: #ResponsiveOrg Copenhagen
organizer.name: Magnus Christensson

description:
Det här är en grupp för alla som är intresserade av filosofin, praktiken eller ekonomin och vetenskapen bakom individuell frihet och ett fritt samhälle.


Här tar vi upp roliga engagemang och tilställningar för de som gillar frihet: öl- och disussionskvällar, debatter, aktivism och fester, eller något annat som någon tycker skulle vara intressant att göra.


Om du är intresserad av libertarianism, anarkokapitalism, agorism, minarkism, utträde ur staten, frihetliga lösningar på komplexa samhällsproblem och gillar att träffa andra som delar den politiska inställningar är det här en perfekt grupp för dig.

description:
Meetup med alle interesserede i åben offentlig data. Koderne, de offentligt ansatte, designerne, akademikerne, entreprenørerne. Kun ved at forbinde og udforske mulighederne sammen bliver det muligt at tilgængeliggøre mere data og skabe eksempler, der vil få andre statslige organisationer til at indse potentialet i åben offentlig data.

Meet-up with all those interested in open government data. The coders, the civil servants, the designers, the academics, the entrepreneurs. Only by connecting and exploring steps together will it be possible to both get more data available, as well as build the examples that will make other government organisations see the potential of open government data.

When you Tweet about CPH Data Drinks please use the tag #cphdd

category.name: movements/politics
description:
Vi vil gerne invitere alle mennesker som ønsker at forandre og påvirke måden vi arbejder på i virksomhederne. De der synes arbejde er noget man gør, og ikke et sted man tager hen. Hvis du har det sådan vil du synes det er interessant at deltage i vores arrangementer og bidrage til diskussionerne vi har på vores meetups.

Hvis du er typen som konstant forsøger at påvirke kulturen i din virksomhed fra de faste planlagte rammer til en mere eksperimenterende samarbejdsform, fra at være kontrolleret mod at være mere autonom – så er #ResponsiveOrg et forum for dig.

Vi vil gerne bringe innovative forandrings-søgende mennesker sammen til #responsivecoffee og andre #responsiveorg arrangementer. Vi håber at du vil dele erfaringer og få ny viden du kan tage med hjem til din virksomhed, og at du får indsigt i hvilke metoder, betingelser og kommunikationsplatforme der kan anvendes for at opnå en Responsive Organisation. Og vi vil gerne dele praktiske erfaringer med at implementere disse.

Kundernes behov og vaner ændrer sig hurtigt, og det kan være enormt svært at følge med som virksomhed, og skabe den forandring og udvikling i virksomheden der er nødvendig for at følge kundernes tempo. The Responsive Organisation meetup er en samling af mennesker som deler og drøfter hvordan de hver især sætter retning og nye standarder for hvordan virksomheder lærer af og tilpasser sig de forandringer der sker i verden. - se ResponsiveOrg præsentation

Vi synes det skal diskuteres face-to-face hvordan vi håndterer det i København – Danmark. Du kan læse mere om Responsive Organisation initiativet her http://www.theresponsiveorg.com/

Vi glæder os til at se dig til vores arrangementer.
name: #ResponsiveOrg Copenhagen

category.name: movements/politics
description:
Swedizen - a Non-state Voluntary Initiative - is a group for anyone interested in creating future stateless cryptonations and open governance. This specific group is based in Stockholm, Sweden, and will try to establish a local "Bitnation compatible" group of people to begin with.


"In the multi-local society, communities and places are junctions of a network, points of connection among short networks, which generate and regenerate the local social and production fabric and long networks, which connect that place and that community with the rest of the world (De Rita, Bonomi, 1998)."

WHAT IT IS:

- Pseudo-anonymous or actual identification of a person, and proof-of-existence.

- Encrypted, trust-based.

- Using GnuPG, NFC and QR technologies.

- Possibility to restore lost password through trusted parties.


WHAT IT'S NOT:

- It is not Government issued or considered a valid form of ID in any state.

- Not a payment system

- Not a cryptocurrency  (and does not need one)

- Not anything money-ish

category.name: movements/politics
description:
Swedizen - a Non-state Voluntary Initiative - is a group for anyone interested in creating future stateless cryptonations and open governance. This specific group is based in Stockholm, Sweden, and will try to establish a local "Bitnation compatible" group of people to begin with.


"In the multi-local society, communities and places are junctions of a network, points of connection among short networks, which generate and regenerate the local social and production fabric and long networks, which connect that place and that community with the rest of the world (De Rita, Bonomi, 1998)."

WHAT IT IS:

- Pseudo-anonymous or actual identification of a person, and proof-of-existence.

- Encrypted, trust-based.

- Using GnuPG, NFC and QR technologies.

- Possibility to restore lost password through trusted parties.


WHAT IT'S NOT:

- It is not Government issued or considered a valid form of ID in any state.

- Not a payment system

- Not a cryptocurrency  (and does not need one)

- Not anything money-ish
name: Swedizen Non-state Voluntary Initiative and Cryptonation

description:
Det här är en grupp för alla som är intresserade av filosofin, praktiken eller ekonomin och vetenskapen bakom individuell frihet och ett fritt samhälle.


Här tar vi upp roliga engagemang och tilställningar för de som gillar frihet: öl- och disussionskvällar, debatter, aktivism och fester, eller något annat som någon tycker skulle vara intressant att göra.


Om du är intresserad av libertarianism, anarkokapitalism, agorism, minarkism, utträde ur staten, frihetliga lösningar på komplexa samhällsproblem och gillar att träffa andra som delar den politiska inställningar är det här en perfekt grupp för dig.

category.name: movements/politics
description:
Swedizen - a Non-state Voluntary Initiative - is a group for anyone interested in creating future stateless cryptonations and open governance. This specific group is based in Stockholm, Sweden, and will try to establish a local "Bitnation compatible" group of people to begin with.


"In the multi-local society, communities and places are junctions of a network, points of connection among short networks, which generate and regenerate the local social and production fabric and long networks, which connect that place and that community with the rest of the world (De Rita, Bonomi, 1998)."

WHAT IT IS:

- Pseudo-anonymous or actual identification of a person, and proof-of-existence.

- Encrypted, trust-based.

- Using GnuPG, NFC and QR technologies.

- Possibility to restore lost password through trusted parties.


WHAT IT'S NOT:

- It is not Government issued or considered a valid form of ID in any state.

- Not a payment system

- Not a cryptocurrency  (and does not need one)

- Not anything money-ish
name: Swedizen Non-state Voluntary Initiative and Cryptonation

Anyone who wants to learn more about Effective Altruism, get to know other people who are passionate about having a positive impact in the world and wants to have deep intriguing discussions should definitely join us! Effective Altruism is a philosophy and social movement which is all about answering one simple question: How can we use our resources to help others as much as possible? Rather than just doing what feels right, we use evidence and careful analysis to find the very best causes to work on. This can apply to everything from where to donate your charity money to future career choice. For more information, please check out the following websites:

description:
Meetup med alle interesserede i åben offentlig data. Koderne, de offentligt ansatte, designerne, akademikerne, entreprenørerne. Kun ved at forbinde og udforske mulighederne sammen bliver det muligt at tilgængeliggøre mere data og skabe eksempler, der vil få andre statslige organisationer til at indse potentialet i åben offentlig data.

Meet-up with all those interested in open government data. The coders, the civil servants, the designers, the academics, the entrepreneurs. Only by connecting and exploring steps together will it be possible to both get more data available, as well as build the examples that will make other government organisations see the potential of open government data.

Data Drinks: Where (free) beer is transmogrified into free data!

When you Tweet about CPH Data Drinks please use the tag #cphdd

category.name: movements/politics
description:
Vi vil gerne invitere alle mennesker som ønsker at forandre og påvirke måden vi arbejder på i virksomhederne. De der synes arbejde er noget man gør, og ikke et sted man tager hen. Hvis du har det sådan vil du synes det er interessant at deltage i vores arrangementer og bidrage til diskussionerne vi har på vores meetups.

Hvis du er typen som konstant forsøger at påvirke kulturen i din virksomhed fra de faste planlagte rammer til en mere eksperimenterende samarbejdsform, fra at være kontrolleret mod at være mere autonom – så er #ResponsiveOrg et forum for dig.

Vi vil gerne bringe innovative forandrings-søgende mennesker sammen til #responsivecoffee og andre #responsiveorg arrangementer. Vi håber at du vil dele erfaringer og få ny viden du kan tage med hjem til din virksomhed, og at du får indsigt i hvilke metoder, betingelser og kommunikationsplatforme der kan anvendes for at opnå en Responsive Organisation. Og vi vil gerne dele praktiske erfaringer med at implementere disse.

Kundernes behov og vaner ændrer sig hurtigt, og det kan være enormt svært at følge med som virksomhed, og skabe den forandring og udvikling i virksomheden der er nødvendig for at følge kundernes tempo. The Responsive Organisation meetup er en samling af mennesker som deler og drøfter hvordan de hver især sætter retning og nye standarder for hvordan virksomheder lærer af og tilpasser sig de forandringer der sker i verden. - se ResponsiveOrg præsentation

Vi synes det skal diskuteres face-to-face hvordan vi håndterer det i København – Danmark. Du kan læse mere om Responsive Organisation initiativet her http://www.theresponsiveorg.com/

Vi glæder os til at se dig til vores arrangementer.
name: #ResponsiveOrg Copenhagen
